list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: - Decoupling Client and Server to become it's own standalone API and terminal support and other features are being moved to terminal module

task.summary: Default task

Big changes, though small to the average user.
- Refactored lots of code - Fixed lots of bugs with terminal usage - Added color support - Updated libraries such as JANSI and Jline - Still needs lots more refactoring of code - Settings now uses reflection and annotations to point to setting values, making less hard coded and static values and cleaner code - SettingsManager has been replaced by GsonConfig<> - Moved more threads async and attempted to fix more spaghetti code (Make less code dependant on each other and more modular)

- Did a lot refractoring of code - Uses JSON (with encryption) while wrapping around an unencrypted JSON block - Uses RSA for handshake encryption - While messing with code, I saw the old encryption method was redundant because the key was given in plain text. This was fixed while also using JSON for sending packets. The packets are now wrapped around a JSON packet wrapper that converts the object into it's own JSON object. - Attempted to lower some latency with more async code - Added some changes to the LightReader API which is planned to become it's own github repo soon. (And so will PiAnimation) - The LightReader API uses annotations for defining it's command name and required arguments.
- Flutter
- Does not allow the server to work correctly
Preparing for release

- Changed to a PacketRegistry system to allow for cross platform usage (packetname : packet.class) - Fixed a bug that caused the client to print an exception when sending a message before it was successfully registered - Added Alibaba FAST_JSON support (config setting) Gson is still default - Added MultiCast gracefully shut down.
- Fixed AutoComplete support - Fixed Debug mode - Fixed File Logger and is now on Client support
- Fixed a bug causing the native transports for Linux and Mac not being included in jar
- Version bump

- Moved to gradle - Removed redundant Main classes - Using https://github.com/Fernthedev/FernUtils - Improved Server start time using parallel tasks - Improved server performance - Improved connection establishment speed - Cleaned old code - Removed lots of old redundancy - Uses now semantic version - MultiCast checks if server's minimum version matches client's version requirements and vice-versa - When establishing connections, the server and client exchange their version data and requirements and each check if the range match requirements. If not, it shows a warning - MulticastServer sleep timing lowered - Added gradle CI

- Flutter work done
- Remove maven.yml
- Attempting to fix CI
- Removed unnecessary Base64 encoding/decoding when encrypting - Bumped version and minimum version to show warning since Base64 encoding/decoding is used on older versions
- Error handling in GSON Encoder
- Made useless field packetName transient to make Packet size smaller by ignoring in serialization

- Clients are now able to auto-fill password with HashedPasswordPacket. This requires the password to be hashed, whether the packet is encrypted or not. SelfMessagePacket with FillMessagePacket is sent, it should receive a MessagePacket in return or HashedPasswordPacket with the password hashed. If password given is incorrect, SelfMessagePacket.MessageType.INCORRECT_PASSWORD_ATTEMPT is sent. If authentication finishes with incorrect password, SelfMessagePacket.MessageType.INCORRECT_PASSWORD_FAILURE is sent.
